article.headline: New Hampshire 69, Binghamton 60
article.story: BINGHAMTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Craig Walls scored 16 points as New Hampshire beat Binghamton 69-60 Sunday in America East basketball. New Hampshire (6-9, 2-4 AE) had three players in double figures, including Mike Christensen with 10 points and 12 rebounds and Ioannis Karalis with 13 points. The Wildcats built a 12-point halftime margin, 38-26, but Binghamton (4-11, 1-5) came back in the second half to take a 52-51 lead with 4:18 to play on a jumper by Troy Hailey. New Hampshire outscored Binghamton 18-7 to end the game, with 11 of those points coming from the free-throw line. Andre Heard led Binghamton with 13 points and Billy Williams scored 12.
